    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-06-25T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-06-25T18:00:00-05:00" n="1058"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1058">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.48/6–1847: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-06-25T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 25, 1947—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>775. Definite authorization re negotiation relief agreement can be sent quickly
                    (Reurtel 1324 June 18 repeated Shanghai 548) upon receipt of reply to Deptel 738
                    June 17. Proposed text of relief agreement being negotiated with Italy being
                    sent in immediately following cable<note n="46" xml:id="d1058fn1">Telegram No.
                        776, June 25, 7 p.m., not printed; for text of agreement between the United
                        States and Italy regarding relief assistance, signed at Rome on July 4,
                        1947, see Department of State Treaties and Other International Acts Series
                        No. 1653, or 61 Stat. (pt. 3) 3135.</note> based largely on terms of relief
                    Act. Ur comments and suggestions for modification to meet situation in China are
                    desired. Sent Nanking as Depts 775 repeated to Shanghai as Depts 1060.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
